{"lemma": "دَبُّورٌ", "slug": "دَبُّورٌ", "root": "د.ب.ر", "root_slug": "د-ب-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/د-ب-ر", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 2}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n12011"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%91%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "wasp", "fa": "زنبور", "ur": "تند ہوا", "tr": "arı", "id": "tawon", "bn": "তনকা", "es": "avispa", "fr": "guêpe", "de": "Wespe", "ru": "оса", "zh": "黄蜂"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "wasp, hornet"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of دَبَرَ (dabara) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "From Proto-Semitic *dVbr- (bee). Cognate with Biblical Hebrew דְּבוֹרָה (dəḇorɔ), Classical Syriac ܕܒܘܪܐ (debbōrā), Amharic ዲቧራ (dibʷara) and Aramaic דְּבוֹרְתָא."}, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n12011", "headword_ar": "دَبُورٌ", "root": "dbx", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", used as a subst. and as an epithet, [of the fem. gender,] so that one says either"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "riyHu Ald~abuwri", "text_ar": "رِيحُ الدَّبُورِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "riyHN dabuwrN", "text_ar": "رِيحٌ دَبُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and simply"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dabuwrN", "text_ar": "دَبُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but more commonly used as an epithet, (M,) [The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "west wind:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a westerly wind:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the west being regarded as the hinder quarter:] the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wind that is opposite to that called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlS~abaA", "text_ar": "الصَّبَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, L, Msb, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alqabuwlu", "text_ar": "القَبُولُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (L,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "blowing from the direction of the place of sunset:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, Msb:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wind that comes from"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the direction of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the back,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hinder part, of the Kaabeh, going towards the place of sunrise:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M:) but IAth rejects this explanation: (TA:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wind that comes from the quarter behind a person when he is standing at the kibleh:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[but this is a most strange explanation:] or, accord. to IAar, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wind that blows from the tract extending from the place where En-Nesr et-Táïr"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Aquila"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sets"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. about W. 10° N. in Central Arabia]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to the place where Suheyl"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Canopus"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rises"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[about S. 29° E. in Central Arabia]: (M:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that comes from the direction of the south"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aljanuwb", "text_ar": "الجَنُوب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "),"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "going towards the place of sunrise:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) it is the worst of winds: it is said that it does not fecundate trees, nor raise clouds: (Meyd, TA:) and in a trad. it is said that the tribe of 'Ád was destroyed by it: (T, TA:) it blows only in the hot season, and is very thirsty: (TA voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nakobaA='u", "text_ar": "نَكْبَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "duburN", "text_ar": "دُبُرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dabaAy^iru", "text_ar": "دَبَايِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (M.) [Hence the saying,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaSafato dabuwruhu wasaqaTato Eabuwruhu", "text_ar": "عَصَفَتْ دَبُورُهُ وَسَقَطَتْ عَبُورُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "His west wind,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "westerly wind, blew violently, and his Sirius set:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his evil fortune prevailed, and his good fortune departed:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dbwr", "text_ar": "دبور"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the worst of winds, as observed above, and Sirius sets aurorally in the beginning of winter, when provisions become scarce]. (A.)       -A2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daborN", "text_ar": "دَبْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", last sentence but two."}], "source_refs": ["M", "S", "L", "Msb", "K", "TA", "Meyd", "T"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}